This paper deals with a transportation network pricing problem, which involves assigning tariffs to a subset of arcs in a network. This problem is related to network optimization and game theory, which are typically covered in the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
